<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1991) - "SOLID STATE" GLOW PLUG ANALYSIS GUIDE - "SOLID STATE" GLOW
        PLUG SYSTEM REPLACEMENT PROCEDURES - Installation (Controller Assembly)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="9">
        <title>Installation (Controller Assembly)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bolt control unit onto intake manifold. Tighten to the standard torque of 7 lbf-ft (10 Nm),
                Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600628">6.28</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4600628" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10727" filename="../figcg1/CG10727.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.28 Control Unit Mounting Bolt Torque</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean stud bolt, as required, to assure a good ground. Connect the ground to the intake
                manifold stud bolt, Figures
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600629">6.29</hotlnk> &#38;
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600630">6.30</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4600629" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11738" filename="../figcg1/CG11738.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.29 Ground Connection [S-Series Vehicles]</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4600630" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg6180" filename="../figeg6/EG6180.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.30 Ground Connection [1000, 3000 and 4000 Series Vehicles]</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install main glow plug ring terminal (dark blue/white lead) and tighten, Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600631">6.31</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>BE SURE TO HOLD THE GLOW PLUG WIRES TIGHT AGAINST THE RELAY HOUSING. TIGHTEN THE NUT TO 65
                        LBF-IN &#177; 5 LBF-IN. (88 Nm &#177; 7 Nm).
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4600631" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10729" filename="../figcg1/CG10729.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.31 Glow Plug Lead Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect wait light connector, Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600632">6.32</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>BE SURE TANG ENGAGES SLOT. LISTEN FOR THE CLICK.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4600632" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10730" filename="../figcg1/CG10730.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.32 Wait Light Connector</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the pink ignition lead to the ignition terminal of the control unit, Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600633">6.33</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4600633" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10731" filename="../figcg1/CG10731.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.33 Install Ignition Lead</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install battery lead to the power terminal of the control unit module, Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600634">6.34</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4600634" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10732" filename="../figcg1/CG10732.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.34 Battery Lead Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the protective cover, Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600635">6.35</hotlnk>. Align the tangs of the cover with the slots on the control
                unit module and push down until the tangs are secured in the slots. Reinstall the air cleaner and
                housing.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4600635" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10733" filename="../figcg1/CG10733.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.35 Protective Cover Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect the negative ground of the battery, Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600636">6.36</hotlnk>, and perform Test F (functional test) on the "Solid State' Glow
                Plug System Troubleshooting Guide" (Form No. CGED-470-*).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4600636" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10721" filename="../figcg1/CG10721.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.36 Reconnect Battery</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
